<info>
Armenia is landlocked country in region of Caucasus, located between Turkey and Georgia.
It has rich ancient heritage, with first armenian state dating back to 860 BC.
Armenia became first state to adopt Christianity as its state religion in 301,
Armenian Apostolic Church exists to this day.

Armenian traits are Patriotic and Cultural, to represent its ancient christian heritage
and today's diplomatic and military struggle with Azerbaijan.

Armenian leaders include ancient leaders of armenian states and from modern republics.
Armenian color is orange from its flag, this is also its flag - flag of Republic of Armenia.
</info>
